modules.description: This module implements an asynchronous session manager using a cookie-based interface, providing functions to create, retrieve, update, and delete sessions backed by a storage system. It operates on session data with string keys and values, and time-to-live periods in seconds, exposing operations like session generation, cookie header parsing, and session expiration control. Concrete use cases include managing authenticated user sessions over HTTP with automatic expiry and cookie synchronization.

This module implements an asynchronous session manager using cookie-based storage, offering operations to generate, parse, and manage sessions with string-keyed data and time-to-live settings. It works with HTTP cookie headers and session stores that support async I/O, enabling use cases like stateful web sessions with automatic expiration and secure cookie handling.

This module provides functions to create, validate, and expire sessions using HTTP cookies with asynchronous storage backends. It operates on session data represented as key-value pairs with optional time-to-live (TTL) constraints, and integrates directly with HTTP cookie headers for transmission. Concrete use cases include managing authenticated user sessions in web applications with automatic session expiration and secure cookie handling.
